1. # POC Overview

The main goal of this project is to provide comprehensive capabilities for managing and tracking datasets within the platform. This will enable users to answer questions like:  "What specific data was this model trained on?" or "Which source documents did this RAG-generated answer come from?". 

Data Lineage will require tracking of datasets across multiple data utilisation flows (Ingestion, Transformation, Training, Inference) covering a range of system touch-points (Feast/MLFlow/Kube Flow Pipeline/LLamastack, Ray, Spark/etc). Lineage events should be automatically generated and captured without requiring explicit actions on the part of the user. 

*A key activity here will be to identify the most appropriate meta-data store for persisting the dataset and lineage data.*

Some questions to understand are:

* Availability of an existing open source data lineage product/UI?  
* Suitability of open standards like Open Lineage?  
* How to integrate existing technologies into an integrated solution (OpenLineage)?  
* Which system should act as the source of truth (meta-data repo)?

It is also critical to keep the parallel and complimentary activities (e.g. DataHub) in consideration for all investigations.

